description:
a new release of the software tool that includes newly developed algorithms housed along
previously released ones within a single user interface.
The new functionalities are:
CCS raw data converter (iEdison No. 0685901-23-0100), IPID 32762-E.
IM-MS-DDA converter and data format (iEdison No. 0685901-23-0099), IPID 32761-E.
The previously developed functionalities are:
PNNL-PreProcessor, IPID 31727-E.
2DLC-MS to LC-IM-MS data file converter, IPID 32136-E.
IMS data file transformations, IPID 32137-E.
Remarks about the PNNL-PreProcessor:
Directly reads Agilent MassHunter (.d) data files and generates new Agilent MassHunter (.d) data files with
enhanced raw signal quality and/or transformed data. Can also process UIMF files.
Has both command-line and graphical user interfaces.
PNNL provides the software executable, freely available for download (https://pnnl-comp-massspec.github.io/PNNL-PreProcessor) and it can be utilized by Agilent customers for non-commercial use.
The source code is not publicly available, an internal source code repository is maintained at PNNL
